<?xml version="1.0"?>
<XML ID="EQInterfaceDefinitionLanguage">
	<Schema xmlns="EverQuestData" xmlns:dt="EverQuestDataTypes" />

	<!-- Custom quick-launch bar: one-click access to the Starfall native
	     windows (Advanced Loot, Persona, Celestial Bank). There is no editable
	     client resource for the built-in EQ-button cascade menu, so this is a
	     small always-visible native window instead — same SIDL + WndNotification
	     pattern as EQUI_NativePersonaWnd.xml / EQUI_NativeCelestialBankWnd.xml.
	     Each button is a one-click open/close TOGGLE (see custom_menu_feature.cpp);
	     gold accent color ties this window's branding to the multi-select
	     highlight used in the Celestial Bank window.

	     Two columns, buttons ordered alphabetically by label reading top-to-
	     bottom then left-to-right: column 1 (X=8) holds Achievements/Advanced
	     Loot/Autoskill/Autospell/Celestial Bank/Collections; column 2 (X=152)
	     continues with Factions/Parcels/Persona/Pet Equipment/Pets/Help.
	     Both columns have 6 rows now — the window's overall height is sized
	     to fit 6 rows. Adding a new button: pick its alphabetical slot, shift
	     everything after it down one row (and into column 2 if column 1
	     overflows past 6, or grow the window if column 2 overflows past 6).

	     Help occupies the LAST slot (152,168), out of strict alphabetical
	     order, because it directly replaced the Chat Timestamps button there
	     (moving it to its correct alphabetical slot would have meant
	     reshuffling every button after Collections) — chat timestamp
	     toggling moved to a plain #timestamps command (documented inside the
	     new Help window itself) since it no longer has a toolbar button. -->

